1. Similarities:
      All have the same win condition
      All have the same deck of cards
      Same dealing methods
      
    Differences:
      Their play methods are different (different legality checkers)
      Different board sizes
      Different point values
      
2. The ElevensBoard extends the Board class, allowing the ElevensBoard to use the super() method to 
    make calls to methods in the Board class. This allows the ElevensBoard to set instance variables in the board class.
    
3. No, they do not cover point value differences.
